5. Get Transaction History (Wallet API)

A wallet isn‚Äôt complete without a transaction history. Moralis can fetch transactions involving the address. This can include native cryptocurrency transfers and optionally internal transactions. There are also separate endpoints for token transfers (ERC-20 and NFT transfers), but here we‚Äôll illustrate the basic native transaction history.
	‚Ä¢	Endpoint: GET /api/v2.2/:address ‚Äì Note: this base endpoint returns native transactions for the address, ordered by block (desc by default) Ôøº.
	‚Ä¢	Query Parameters:
	‚Ä¢	chain ‚Äì the chain to query (e.g., eth, 0x1, etc.) Ôøº.
	‚Ä¢	Filtering by block or date:
	‚Ä¢	from_block / to_block ‚Äì to get transactions between certain block numbers Ôøº.
	‚Ä¢	from_date / to_date ‚Äì to get transactions in a date range (if both block and date are provided, block takes precedence) Ôøº.
